  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Electromagnetic waves propagating in a slab waveguide, whose walls consist of three-dimensional topological insulator, experience a topological cutoff frequency, <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow></msub></math> . Once <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow></msub></math> depends upon the penetration length of the metallic surface states into the bulk, l , our findings suggest TI-made waveguides as useful apparatus to estimate the microscopic quantity l by measuring the optical response carried out by the macroscopic signature of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>θ</mi></mrow></msub></math> .</subfield>
